    <p><strong>Rule of thumb:</strong> A mixer bowl should never be more than 60–70% full during operation. Overfilling strains the motor and leads to uneven mixing. If you need 15 kg of bread dough per batch, buy a 30-litre mixer — not a 20-litre one.</p>
    <p>In Indian commercial bakeries, the 20-litre and 30-litre sizes are the most popular for planetary mixers. For spiral mixers, 30-litre and 60-litre are the sweet spots for most medium to large bakeries.</p>

    <h2>5. Energy Use: Which Mixer Costs More to Run?</h2>
    <p>Spiral mixers are generally more energy-efficient per kilogram of dough produced. Here's why: the bowl-rotating mechanism is mechanically simpler and puts less strain on the motor than the planetary motion. A spiral mixer's motor runs at lower relative load when processing full-capacity bread dough batches compared to a planetary mixer working on the same load.</p>

